    "# 37. The Equipment Selection Problem (RTG vs. RMG vs. Straddle)\n",
    "## Tier 2: Constraint Propagation with Backtracking Algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "### Goal\n",
    "Implement a systematic backtracking algorithm with constraint propagation to explore the complex equipment selection solution space while efficiently pruning infeasible combinations early in the search process.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Assumptions\n",
    "- Equipment selection involves multiple interdependent constraints (budget, capacity, compatibility)\n",
    "- Constraint domains can be reduced through logical inference and propagation\n",
    "- Early pruning of infeasible branches significantly improves search efficiency\n",
    "- Solution quality can be ranked using composite scoring functions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Approach (Step-by-Step)\n",
    "1. **Define Constraint Domains**: Establish feasible ranges for each equipment type and quantity\n",
    "2. **Implement Consistency Checking**: Verify partial solutions satisfy all constraints\n",
    "3. **Constraint Propagation**: Reduce search space by inferring implied constraints\n",
    "4. **Backtracking Search**: Systematically explore solution space with intelligent pruning\n",
    "5. **Solution Ranking**: Evaluate and rank feasible solutions using multi-criteria scoring\n",
    "\n",
    "### What to Look for in the Results\n",
    "- Complete search tree visualization showing exploration and pruning decisions\n",
    "- Efficiency metrics comparing constraint propagation vs. naive backtracking\n",
    "- Ranked solutions with detailed constraint satisfaction analysis\n",
    "- Performance comparison with mathematical optimization baseline\n",
    "\n",
    "### Concrete Example\n",
    "Mediterranean Container Terminal with 8 blocks:\n",
    "- Budget constraint: \$180 million total investment\n",
    "- Capacity requirement: 2,400 moves per day minimum\n",
    "- Block-specific constraints: compatibility and operational synergy requirements\n",
    "- Equipment quantity ranges: RTG (8-20), RMG (6-12), Straddle (16-32)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why this Tier Exists vs. Tier 1\n",
    "**Constraint Propagation provides:**\n",
    "- **Complex constraint handling**: Manages interdependent rules and logical relationships\n",
    "- **Early pruning**: Eliminates infeasible solutions before full evaluation\n",
    "- **Search efficiency**: Dramatically reduces computational complexity for large problems\n",
    "- **Flexibility**: Easily accommodates new constraints and business rules\n",
    "\n",
    "**Advantages over Mathematical Optimization:**\n",
    "- Handles complex logical constraints that are difficult to formulate mathematically\n",
    "- Provides complete enumeration of all feasible solutions\n",
    "- More intuitive for business users to understand and modify constraints\n",
    "- Better scalability for problems with many discrete variables\n",
    "\n",
    "**When to use this Tier:**\n",
    "- Problems with complex rule-based constraints and compatibility requirements\n",
    "- Situations requiring complete enumeration of feasible solutions\n",
    "- Decision contexts with frequently changing business rules\n",
    "- Medium-sized problems where mathematical optimization becomes computationally expensive"
   ]
